sentence: (+) Viacom ( VIA ), which was up more than 6% after it agreed to acquire Pluto TV, a free streaming television service, for $340 million.
(+) Procter & Gamble ( PG ) was up over 4% as i t report ed earnings and revenue in its fiscal second quarter that topped expectations while raising its guidance for 2019.
The company said earnings came in at $1.25 a share, up from $1.19 during the same quarter last year and ahead of consensus compiled by Capital IQ for $1.21 a share.

(-) Kimberly-Clark ( KMB ) was declining by more than 4% after the consumer products company posted Q4 adjusted earnings of $1.60 per diluted share, up from $1.57 per share a year ago but below the $1.66 average estimate from analysts polled by Capital IQ.
